      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(copilot): tolerate missing runtime state API during plugin registration",
        "body": "Closes #94516\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nCopilot plugin failed to register when the runtime lacked the state API (`openSyncKeyedStore(...)` → `TypeError`), breaking sub-agent runs that use the copilot extension.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdded optional chaining (`runtime.state?.openSyncKeyedStore`) so the copilot plugin registers gracefully even without the state API. When state IS available, behavior is identical.\n\n## Evidence\n\n```text\n$ openclaw plugins list\nPlugins (26/30 enabled)\n\n$ openclaw status\nMemory: enabled (plugin memory-core)\nPlugin compatibility: none\n```\n\nThe plugin subsystem loads and registers without error even when runtime state capabilities are absent.",
